37static /*@only@*/ yasm_arch *
38x86_create(const char *machine, const char *parser,
39 /*@out@*/ yasm_arch_create_error *error)
40{
41 yasm_arch_x86 *arch_x86;
42 unsigned int amd64_machine, address_size;
43
44 *error = YASM_ARCH_CREATE_OK;
45
46 if (yasm__strcasecmp(machine, "x86") == 0) {
47 amd64_machine = 0;
48 address_size = 32;
49 } else if (yasm__strcasecmp(machine, "amd64") == 0) {
50 amd64_machine = 1;
51 address_size = 64;
52 } else if (yasm__strcasecmp(machine, "x32") == 0) {
53 amd64_machine = 1;
54 address_size = 32;
55 }
56 else {
57 *error = YASM_ARCH_CREATE_BAD_MACHINE;
58 return NULL;
59 }
60
61 arch_x86 = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(yasm_arch_x86));
62
63 arch_x86->arch.module = &yasm_x86_LTX_arch;
64
65 /* default to all instructions/features enabled */
66 arch_x86->active_cpu = 0;
67 arch_x86->cpu_enables_size = 1;
68 arch_x86->cpu_enables = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(wordptr));
69 arch_x86->cpu_enables[0] = BitVector_Create(64, FALSE);
70 BitVector_Fill(arch_x86->cpu_enables[0]);
71
72 arch_x86->amd64_machine = amd64_machine;
73 arch_x86->mode_bits = 0;
74 arch_x86->address_size = address_size;
75 arch_x86->force_strict = 0;
76 arch_x86->default_rel = 0;
77 arch_x86->gas_intel_mode = 0;
78 arch_x86->nop = X86_NOP_BASIC;
79
80 if (yasm__strcasecmp(parser, "nasm") == 0)
81 arch_x86->parser = X86_PARSER_NASM;
82 else if (yasm__strcasecmp(parser, "tasm") == 0)
83 arch_x86->parser = X86_PARSER_TASM;
84 else if (yasm__strcasecmp(parser, "gas") == 0
85 || yasm__strcasecmp(parser, "gnu") == 0)
86 arch_x86->parser = X86_PARSER_GAS;
87 else {
88 yasm_xfree(arch_x86);
89 *error = YASM_ARCH_CREATE_BAD_PARSER;
90 return NULL;
91 }
92
93 return (yasm_arch *)arch_x86;
94}
95
96static void
97x86_destroy(/*@only@*/ yasm_arch *arch)
98{
99 yasm_arch_x86 *arch_x86 = (yasm_arch_x86 *)arch;
100 unsigned int i;
101 for (i=0; i<arch_x86->cpu_enables_size; i++)
102 BitVector_Destroy(arch_x86->cpu_enables[i]);
103 yasm_xfree(arch_x86->cpu_enables);
104 yasm_xfree(arch);
105}
106
107static const char *
108x86_get_machine(const yasm_arch *arch)
109{
110 const yasm_arch_x86 *arch_x86 = (const yasm_arch_x86 *)arch;
111 if (arch_x86->amd64_machine) {
112 if (arch_x86->address_size == 32)
113 return "x32";
114 else
115 return "amd64";
116 } else
117 return "x86";
118}
119
120static unsigned int
121x86_get_address_size(const yasm_arch *arch)
122{
123 const yasm_arch_x86 *arch_x86 = (const yasm_arch_x86 *)arch;
124 if (arch_x86->mode_bits != 0)
125 return arch_x86->mode_bits;
126 return arch_x86->address_size;
127}
128
129static int
130x86_set_var(yasm_arch *arch, const char *var, unsigned long val)
131{
132 yasm_arch_x86 *arch_x86 = (yasm_arch_x86 *)arch;
133 if (yasm__strcasecmp(var, "mode_bits") == 0)
134 arch_x86->mode_bits = (unsigned int)val;
135 else if (yasm__strcasecmp(var, "force_strict") == 0)
136 arch_x86->force_strict = (unsigned int)val;
137 else if (yasm__strcasecmp(var, "default_rel") == 0) {
138 if (arch_x86->mode_bits != 64)
139 yasm_warn_set(YASM_WARN_GENERAL,
140 N_("ignoring default rel in non-64-bit mode"));
141 else
142 arch_x86->default_rel = (unsigned int)val;
143 } else if (yasm__strcasecmp(var, "gas_intel_mode") == 0) {
144 arch_x86->gas_intel_mode = (unsigned int)val;
145 } else
146 return 1;
147 return 0;
148}

150static void
151x86_dir_cpu(yasm_object *object, yasm_valparamhead *valparams,
152 yasm_valparamhead *objext_valparams, unsigned long line)
153{
154 yasm_arch_x86 *arch_x86 = (yasm_arch_x86 *)object->arch;
155
156 yasm_valparam *vp;
157 yasm_vps_foreach(vp, valparams) {
158 /*@null@*/ /*@dependent@*/ const char *s = yasm_vp_string(vp);
159 if (s)
160 yasm_x86__parse_cpu(arch_x86, s, strlen(s));
161 else if (vp->type == YASM_PARAM_EXPR) {
162 const yasm_intnum *intcpu;
163 intcpu = yasm_expr_get_intnum(&vp->param.e, 0);
164 if (!intcpu)
165 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX,
166 N_("invalid argument to [%s]"), "CPU");
167 else {
168 char strcpu[16];
169 sprintf(strcpu, "%lu", yasm_intnum_get_uint(intcpu));
170 yasm_x86__parse_cpu(arch_x86, strcpu, strlen(strcpu));
171 }
172 } else
173 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_SYNTAX, N_("invalid argument to [%s]"),
174 "CPU");
175 }
176}
177
178static void
179x86_dir_bits(yasm_object *object, yasm_valparamhead *valparams,
180 yasm_valparamhead *objext_valparams, unsigned long line)
181{
182 yasm_arch_x86 *arch_x86 = (yasm_arch_x86 *)object->arch;
183 yasm_valparam *vp;
184 /*@only@*/ /*@null@*/ yasm_expr *e = NULL;
185 const yasm_intnum *intn;
186 long lval;
187
188 if ((vp = yasm_vps_first(valparams)) && !vp->val &&
189 (e = yasm_vp_expr(vp, object->symtab, line)) != NULL &&
190 (intn = yasm_expr_get_intnum(&e, 0)) != NULL &&
191 (lval = yasm_intnum_get_int(intn)) &&
192 (lval == 16 || lval == 32 || lval == 64))
193 arch_x86->mode_bits = (unsigned char)lval;
194 else
195 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_VALUE, N_("invalid argument to [%s]"),
196 "BITS");
197 if (e)
198 yasm_expr_destroy(e);
199}

225static const unsigned char **
226x86_get_fill(const yasm_arch *arch)
227{
228 const yasm_arch_x86 *arch_x86 = (const yasm_arch_x86 *)arch;
229
230 /* Fill patterns that GAS uses. */
231 static const unsigned char fill16_1[1] =
232 {0x90}; /* 1 - nop */
233 static const unsigned char fill16_2[2] =
234 {0x89, 0xf6}; /* 2 - mov si, si */
235 static const unsigned char fill16_3[3] =
236 {0x8d, 0x74, 0x00}; /* 3 - lea si, [si+byte 0] */
237 static const unsigned char fill16_4[4] =
238 {0x8d, 0xb4, 0x00, 0x00}; /* 4 - lea si, [si+word 0] */
239 static const unsigned char fill16_5[5] =
240 {0x90, /* 5 - nop */
241 0x8d, 0xb4, 0x00, 0x00}; /* lea si, [si+word 0] */
242 static const unsigned char fill16_6[6] =
243 {0x89, 0xf6, /* 6 - mov si, si */
244 0x8d, 0xbd, 0x00, 0x00}; /* lea di, [di+word 0] */
245 static const unsigned char fill16_7[7] =
246 {0x8d, 0x74, 0x00, /* 7 - lea si, [si+byte 0] */
247 0x8d, 0xbd, 0x00, 0x00}; /* lea di, [di+word 0] */
248 static const unsigned char fill16_8[8] =
249 {0x8d, 0xb4, 0x00, 0x00, /* 8 - lea si, [si+word 0] */
250 0x8d, 0xbd, 0x00, 0x00}; /* lea di, [di+word 0] */
251 static const unsigned char fill16_9[9] =
252 {0xeb, 0x07, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, /* 9 - jmp $+9; nop fill */
253 0x90, 0x90, 0x90};
254 static const unsigned char fill16_10[10] =
255 {0xeb, 0x08, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, /* 10 - jmp $+10; nop fill */
256 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90};
257 static const unsigned char fill16_11[11] =
258 {0xeb, 0x09, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, /* 11 - jmp $+11; nop fill */
259 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90};
260 static const unsigned char fill16_12[12] =
261 {0xeb, 0x0a, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, /* 12 - jmp $+12; nop fill */
262 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90};
263 static const unsigned char fill16_13[13] =
264 {0xeb, 0x0b, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, /* 13 - jmp $+13; nop fill */
265 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90};
266 static const unsigned char fill16_14[14] =
267 {0xeb, 0x0c, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, /* 14 - jmp $+14; nop fill */
268 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90};
269 static const unsigned char fill16_15[15] =
270 {0xeb, 0x0d, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, /* 15 - jmp $+15; nop fill */
271 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90};
272 static const unsigned char *fill16[16] =
273 {
274 NULL, fill16_1, fill16_2, fill16_3,
275 fill16_4, fill16_5, fill16_6, fill16_7,
276 fill16_8, fill16_9, fill16_10, fill16_11,
277 fill16_12, fill16_13, fill16_14, fill16_15
278 };
279
280 static const unsigned char fill32_1[1] =
281 {0x90}; /* 1 - nop */
282 static const unsigned char fill32_2[2] =
283 {0x66, 0x90}; /* 2 - xchg ax, ax (o16 nop) */
284 static const unsigned char fill32_3[3] =
285 {0x8d, 0x76, 0x00}; /* 3 - lea esi, [esi+byte 0] */
286 static const unsigned char fill32_4[4] =
287 {0x8d, 0x74, 0x26, 0x00}; /* 4 - lea esi, [esi*1+byte 0] */
288 static const unsigned char fill32_5[5] =
289 {0x90, /* 5 - nop */
290 0x8d, 0x74, 0x26, 0x00}; /* lea esi, [esi*1+byte 0] */
291 static const unsigned char fill32_6[6] =
292 {0x8d, 0xb6, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00};/* 6 - lea esi, [esi+dword 0] */
293 static const unsigned char fill32_7[7] =
294 {0x8d, 0xb4, 0x26, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, /* 7 - lea esi, [esi*1+dword 0] */
295 0x00};
296 static const unsigned char fill32_8[8] =
297 {0x90, /* 8 - nop */
298 0x8d, 0xb4, 0x26, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, /* lea esi, [esi*1+dword 0] */
299 0x00};
300#if 0
301 /* GAS uses these */
302 static const unsigned char fill32_9[9] =
303 {0x89, 0xf6, /* 9 - mov esi, esi */
304 0x8d, 0xbc, 0x27, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, /* lea edi, [edi*1+dword 0] */
305 0x00};
306 static const unsigned char fill32_10[10] =
307 {0x8d, 0x76, 0x00, /* 10 - lea esi, [esi+byte 0] */
308 0x8d, 0xbc, 0x27, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, /* lea edi, [edi+dword 0] */
309 0x00};
310 static const unsigned char fill32_11[11] =
311 {0x8d, 0x74, 0x26, 0x00, /* 11 - lea esi, [esi*1+byte 0] */
312 0x8d, 0xbc, 0x27, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, /* lea edi, [edi*1+dword 0] */
313 0x00};
314 static const unsigned char fill32_12[12] =
315 {0x8d, 0xb6, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, /* 12 - lea esi, [esi+dword 0] */
316 0x8d, 0xbf, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00};/* lea edi, [edi+dword 0] */
317 static const unsigned char fill32_13[13] =
318 {0x8d, 0xb6, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, /* 13 - lea esi, [esi+dword 0] */
319 0x8d, 0xbc, 0x27, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, /* lea edi, [edi*1+dword 0] */
320 0x00};
321 static const unsigned char fill32_14[14] =
322 {0x8d, 0xb4, 0x26, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, /* 14 - lea esi, [esi*1+dword 0] */
323 0x00,
324 0x8d, 0xbc, 0x27, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, /* lea edi, [edi*1+dword 0] */
325 0x00};
326#else
327 /* But on newer processors, these are recommended */
328 static const unsigned char fill32_9[9] =
329 {0xeb, 0x07, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, /* 9 - jmp $+9; nop fill */
330 0x90, 0x90, 0x90};
331 static const unsigned char fill32_10[10] =
332 {0xeb, 0x08, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, /* 10 - jmp $+10; nop fill */
333 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90};
334 static const unsigned char fill32_11[11] =
335 {0xeb, 0x09, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, /* 11 - jmp $+11; nop fill */
336 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90};
337 static const unsigned char fill32_12[12] =
338 {0xeb, 0x0a, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, /* 12 - jmp $+12; nop fill */
339 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90};
340 static const unsigned char fill32_13[13] =
341 {0xeb, 0x0b, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, /* 13 - jmp $+13; nop fill */
342 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90};
343 static const unsigned char fill32_14[14] =
344 {0xeb, 0x0c, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, /* 14 - jmp $+14; nop fill */
345 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90};
346#endif
347 static const unsigned char fill32_15[15] =
348 {0xeb, 0x0d, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, /* 15 - jmp $+15; nop fill */
349 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90, 0x90};
350 static const unsigned char *fill32[16] =
351 {
352 NULL, fill32_1, fill32_2, fill32_3,
353 fill32_4, fill32_5, fill32_6, fill32_7,
354 fill32_8, fill32_9, fill32_10, fill32_11,
355 fill32_12, fill32_13, fill32_14, fill32_15
356 };
357
358 /* Long form nops available on more recent Intel and AMD processors */
359 static const unsigned char fill32new_3[3] =
360 {0x0f, 0x1f, 0x00}; /* 3 - nop(3) */
361 static const unsigned char fill32new_4[4] =
362 {0x0f, 0x1f, 0x40, 0x00}; /* 4 - nop(4) */
363 static const unsigned char fill32new_5[5] =
364 {0x0f, 0x1f, 0x44, 0x00, 0x00}; /* 5 - nop(5) */
365 static const unsigned char fill32new_6[6] =
366 {0x66, 0x0f, 0x1f, 0x44, 0x00, 0x00}; /* 6 - nop(6) */
367 static const unsigned char fill32new_7[7] =
368 {0x0f, 0x1f, 0x80, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00}; /* 7 - nop(7) */
369 static const unsigned char fill32new_8[8] =
370 {0x0f, 0x1f, 0x84, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, /* 8 - nop(8) */
371 0x00};
372 static const unsigned char fill32new_9[9] =
373 {0x66, 0x0f, 0x1f, 0x84, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, /* 9 - nop(9) */
374 0x00, 0x00};
375
376 /* Longer forms preferred by Intel use repeated o16 prefixes */
377 static const unsigned char fill32intel_10[10] =
378 {0x66, 0x2e, 0x0f, 0x1f, 0x84, 0x00, 0x00, /* 10 - o16; cs; nop */
379 0x00, 0x00, 0x00};
380 static const unsigned char fill32intel_11[11] =
381 {0x66, 0x66, 0x2e, 0x0f, 0x1f, 0x84, 0x00, /* 11 - 2x o16; cs; nop */
382 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00};
383 static const unsigned char fill32intel_12[12] =
384 {0x66, 0x66, 0x66, 0x2e, 0x0f, 0x1f, 0x84, /* 12 - 3x o16; cs; nop */
385 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00};
386 static const unsigned char fill32intel_13[13] =
387 {0x66, 0x66, 0x66, 0x66, 0x2e, 0x0f, 0x1f, /* 13 - 4x o16; cs; nop */
388 0x84, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00};
389 static const unsigned char fill32intel_14[14] =
390 {0x66, 0x66, 0x66, 0x66, 0x66, 0x2e, 0x0f, /* 14 - 5x o16; cs; nop */
391 0x1f, 0x84, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00};
392 static const unsigned char fill32intel_15[15] =
393 {0x66, 0x66, 0x66, 0x66, 0x66, 0x66, 0x2e, /* 15 - 6x o16; cs; nop */
394 0x0f, 0x1f, 0x84, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00};
395
396 /* Longer forms preferred by AMD use fewer o16 prefixes and no CS prefix;
397 * Source: Software Optimisation Guide for AMD Family 10h
398 * Processors 40546 revision 3.10 February 2009
399 */
400 static const unsigned char fill32amd_10[10] =
401 {0x66, 0x66, 0x0f, 0x1f, 0x84, 0x00, 0x00, /* 10 - nop(10) */
402 0x00, 0x00, 0x00};
403 static const unsigned char fill32amd_11[11] =
404 {0x0f, 0x1f, 0x44, 0x00, 0x00, /* 11 - nop(5) */
405 0x66, 0x0f, 0x1f, 0x44, 0x00, 0x00}; /* nop(6) */
406 static const unsigned char fill32amd_12[12] =
407 {0x66, 0x0f, 0x1f, 0x44, 0x00, 0x00, /* 12 - nop(6) */
408 0x66, 0x0f, 0x1f, 0x44, 0x00, 0x00}; /* nop(6) */
409 static const unsigned char fill32amd_13[13] =
410 {0x66, 0x0f, 0x1f, 0x44, 0x00, 0x00, /* 13 - nop(6) */
411 0x0f, 0x1f, 0x80, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00}; /* nop(7) */
412 static const unsigned char fill32amd_14[14] =
413 {0x0f, 0x1f, 0x80, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, /* 14 - nop(7) */
414 0x0f, 0x1f, 0x80, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00}; /* nop(7) */
415 static const unsigned char fill32amd_15[15] =
416 {0x0f, 0x1f, 0x80, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, /* 15 - nop(7) */
417 0x0f, 0x1f, 0x84, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00}; /* nop(8) */
418
419 static const unsigned char *fill32_intel[16] =
420 {
421 NULL, fill32_1, fill32_2, fill32new_3,
422 fill32new_4, fill32new_5, fill32new_6, fill32new_7,
423 fill32new_8, fill32new_9, fill32intel_10, fill32intel_11,
424 fill32intel_12, fill32intel_13, fill32intel_14, fill32intel_15
425 };
426 static const unsigned char *fill32_amd[16] =
427 {
428 NULL, fill32_1, fill32_2, fill32new_3,
429 fill32new_4, fill32new_5, fill32new_6, fill32new_7,
430 fill32new_8, fill32new_9, fill32amd_10, fill32amd_11,
431 fill32amd_12, fill32amd_13, fill32amd_14, fill32amd_15
432 };
433
434 switch (arch_x86->mode_bits) {
435 case 16:
436 return fill16;
437 case 32:
438 if (arch_x86->nop == X86_NOP_INTEL)
439 return fill32_intel;
440 else if (arch_x86->nop == X86_NOP_AMD)
441 return fill32_amd;
442 else
443 return fill32;
444 case 64:
445 /* We know long nops are available in 64-bit mode; default to Intel
446 * ones if unspecified (to match GAS behavior).
447 */
448 if (arch_x86->nop == X86_NOP_AMD)
449 return fill32_amd;
450 else
451 return fill32_intel;
452 default:
453 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_VALUE,
454 N_("Invalid mode_bits in x86_get_fill"));
455 return NULL;
456 }
457}

459unsigned int
460yasm_x86__get_reg_size(uintptr_t reg)
461{
462 switch ((x86_expritem_reg_size)(reg & ~0xFUL)) {
463 case X86_REG8:
464 case X86_REG8X:
465 return 8;
466 case X86_REG16:
467 return 16;
468 case X86_REG32:
469 case X86_CRREG:
470 case X86_DRREG:
471 case X86_TRREG:
472 return 32;
473 case X86_REG64:
474 case X86_MMXREG:
475 return 64;
476 case X86_XMMREG:
477 return 128;
478 case X86_YMMREG:
479 return 256;
480 case X86_FPUREG:
481 return 80;
482 default:
483 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_VALUE, N_("unknown register size"));
484 }
485 return 0;
486}
487
488static unsigned int
489x86_get_reg_size(yasm_arch *arch, uintptr_t reg)
490{
491 return yasm_x86__get_reg_size(reg);
492}
493
494static uintptr_t
495x86_reggroup_get_reg(yasm_arch *arch, uintptr_t reggroup,
496 unsigned long regindex)
497{
498 yasm_arch_x86 *arch_x86 = (yasm_arch_x86 *)arch;
499 switch ((x86_expritem_reg_size)(reggroup & ~0xFUL)) {
500 case X86_XMMREG:
501 case X86_YMMREG:
502 if (arch_x86->mode_bits == 64) {
503 if (regindex > 15)
504 return 0;
505 return reggroup | (regindex & 15);
506 }
507 /*@fallthrough@*/
508 case X86_MMXREG:
509 case X86_FPUREG:
510 if (regindex > 7)
511 return 0;
512 return reggroup | (regindex & 7);
513 default:
514 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_VALUE, N_("bad register group"));
515 }
516 return 0;
517}
518
519static void
520x86_reg_print(yasm_arch *arch, uintptr_t reg, FILE *f)
521{
522 static const char *name8[] = {"al","cl","dl","bl","ah","ch","dh","bh"};
523 static const char *name8x[] = {
524 "al", "cl", "dl", "bl", "spl", "bpl", "sil", "dil",
525 "r8b", "r9b", "r10b", "r11b", "r12b", "r13b", "r14b", "r15b"
526 };
527 static const char *name16[] = {
528 "ax", "cx", "dx", "bx", "sp", "bp", "si", "di",
529 "r8w", "r9w", "r10w", "r11w", "r12w", "r13w", "r14w", "r15w"
530 };
531 static const char *name32[] = {
532 "eax", "ecx", "edx", "ebx", "esp", "ebp", "esi", "edi",
533 "r8d", "r9d", "r10d", "r11d", "r12d", "r13d", "r14d", "r15d"
534 };
535 static const char *name64[] = {
536 "rax", "rcx", "rdx", "rbx", "rsp", "rbp", "rsi", "rdi",
537 "r8", "r9", "r10", "r11", "r12", "r13", "r14", "r15"
538 };
539
540 switch ((x86_expritem_reg_size)(reg & ~0xFUL)) {
541 case X86_REG8:
542 fprintf(f, "%s", name8[reg&0xF]);
543 break;
544 case X86_REG8X:
545 fprintf(f, "%s", name8x[reg&0xF]);
546 break;
547 case X86_REG16:
548 fprintf(f, "%s", name16[reg&0xF]);
549 break;
550 case X86_REG32:
551 fprintf(f, "%s", name32[reg&0xF]);
552 break;
553 case X86_REG64:
554 fprintf(f, "%s", name64[reg&0xF]);
555 break;
556 case X86_MMXREG:
557 fprintf(f, "mm%d", (int)(reg&0xF));
558 break;
559 case X86_XMMREG:
560 fprintf(f, "xmm%d", (int)(reg&0xF));
561 break;
562 case X86_YMMREG:
563 fprintf(f, "ymm%d", (int)(reg&0xF));
564 break;
565 case X86_CRREG:
566 fprintf(f, "cr%d", (int)(reg&0xF));
567 break;
568 case X86_DRREG:
569 fprintf(f, "dr%d", (int)(reg&0xF));
570 break;
571 case X86_TRREG:
572 fprintf(f, "tr%d", (int)(reg&0xF));
573 break;
574 case X86_FPUREG:
575 fprintf(f, "st%d", (int)(reg&0xF));
576 break;
577 default:
578 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_VALUE, N_("unknown register size"));
579 }
580}
581
582static void
583x86_segreg_print(yasm_arch *arch, uintptr_t segreg, FILE *f)
584{
585 static const char *name[] = {"es","cs","ss","ds","fs","gs"};
586 fprintf(f, "%s", name[segreg&7]);
587}
